[.](master) $ git remote add origin git@github.com:[ì‚¬ìš©ìì´ë¦„]/[í”„ë¡œì íŠ¸ ë””ë ‰í† ë¦¬].git
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>ì™„ë£Œë˜ì—ˆìœ¼ë©´ ì €ì¥ì†Œì— ì˜¬ë ¤ë³´ë„ë¡ í•œë‹¤. <code class="highlighter-rouge">publish-gitbook.sh</code> ë¼ëŠ” ì‰˜ ìŠ¤í¬ë¦½íŠ¸ë¥¼ ë§Œë“¤ì–´ì¤€ë‹¤.</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>[.](master) $ vi publish-gitbook.sh
</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c">#!/bin/bash</span>

<span class="c"># remove gitbook old things</span>
<span class="nb">rm</span> <span class="nt">-rf</span> _book
<span class="nb">rm</span> <span class="nt">-rf</span> docs

<span class="c"># gitbook init</span>
gitbook <span class="nb">install</span> <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> gitbook build

<span class="c"># build pages</span>
<span class="nb">mkdir </span>docs
<span class="nb">cp</span> <span class="nt">-R</span> _book/<span class="k">*</span> docs/

<span class="c"># delete things</span>
git clean <span class="nt">-fx</span> _book

<span class="c"># upload</span>
git add <span class="nb">.</span>
git commit <span class="nt">-a</span> <span class="nt">-m</span> <span class="s2">"update docs"</span>
git push <span class="nt">-u</span> origin master
</code></pre></div></div>

